PREREQUISITE
		
1) setup docker-compose first
2) make sure your 3306 port is free (mysql service is stop)

RUN THE FOLLOWING COMMAND

1) sudo docker-compose build
2) sudo docker-compose up


UNDERSTANDING

1)container port 8080 bind with local 80, so you can call APIs like
	1) http://localhost:80/count?producer=500&consumer=600
	2) http://localhost:80/count/40

2) there are two table
	1) count_table: to save the count and 0 or 100 value
	2) request_info: to persist the request.


Please let me know if you have any kind of question
